    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3978934897" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3978934897" />
    <a title="Blair" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/10733023-blair"><img alt="Blair" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1640924903p2/10733023.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3978934897?book_show_action=true">May 08, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Blair" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Blair" href="/user/show/10733023-blair">Blair</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10733023-blair?shelf=2021">2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10733023-blair?shelf=spy-fiction">spy-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10733023-blair?shelf=thriller">thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/10733023-blair?shelf=daniel-silva">daniel-silva</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3978934897" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15211986429805219627">Daniel Silva&apos;s The Confessor, #3 in the Gabriel Allon series, is another better than average spy thriller. Mixing fact with fiction, Silva researches, questions, imagines and finally creates a story that stimulates and entertains. And I think that&apos;s why I like this series as much as I do. I was going to call it my guilty pleasure, but hell, i don&apos;t feel guilty. <br/>Gabriel Allon, renowned art restorer and reluctant agent for Israeli intelligence is called in to investigate the murder of Benjamin Ste</span>
  <span id="freeText15211986429805219627" style="display:none">Daniel Silva's The Confessor, #3 in the Gabriel Allon series, is another better than average spy thriller. Mixing fact with fiction, Silva researches, questions, imagines and finally creates a story that stimulates and entertains. And I think that's why I like this series as much as I do. I was going to call it my guilty pleasure, but hell, i don't feel guilty. <br />Gabriel Allon, renowned art restorer and reluctant agent for Israeli intelligence is called in to investigate the murder of Benjamin Stern, a Jewish history professor and friend of Gabriels. He learns that Stern had been commissioned to write a book, a very revelatory one, that if finished and published could shine a new light on the Holocaust, creating a shit storm in its wake.<br />Intricately plotted, with a multitude of characters, from spies, assassins and journalists to nuns, cardinals and the supreme pontiff himself, the story crisscrosses Europe and ventures into the very heart of the Vatican.<br />Educational, enlightening, entertaining, I look forward to more Gabriel Allon.<br />3.75 stars</span>
  <a data-text-id="15211986429805219627" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


